# ðŸ”¹ 1. Run the Backend (MongoDB API)

### Using Docker (Recommended)

1. Open a terminal in the project root (securin-recipe-app-complete/).

2. Start services:

   bash
   docker-compose up -d
   

   * This runs MongoDB (localhost:27017)
   * And your backend (localhost:4001)

3. Seed the database (load recipes):

   bash
   docker exec -it securin-recipe-app-complete-server_mongo-1 \
     node scripts/seed.js
   

4. Verify API is working by visiting:

   * [http://localhost:4001/api/recipes?page=1\&limit=5](http://localhost:4001/api/recipes?page=1&limit=5)
   * [http://localhost:4001/api/recipes/search?ingredient=chicken](http://localhost:4001/api/recipes/search?ingredient=chicken)



### Without Docker (Local Mongo)

1. Start *MongoDB* locally:

   bash
   mongod
   
2. Configure server_mongo/src/db.js:

   js
   const MONGO_URL = "mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/securin_recipes";
   
3. Install dependencies:

   bash
   cd server_mongo
   npm install
   
4. Seed database:

   bash
   node scripts/seed.js
   
5. Run backend:

   bash
   npm run dev
   

   â†’ Backend runs at *[http://localhost:4001](http://localhost:4001)*



 2. Run the Frontend (React App)

1. Open a new terminal.
2. Go into the frontend folder:

   bash
   cd client
   
3. Install dependencies:

   bash
   npm install
   
4. Start frontend:

   bash
   npm run dev
   
5. Open in browser:

   
   http://localhost:5173
   

 Now React app will fetch recipes from backend API (MongoDB).



3. Quick Check

* Backend API â†’ http://localhost:4001/api/recipes
* Frontend UI â†’ http://localhost:5173
